<td bgcolor="#CECECE" class="btext" width="100%"><b>New Opera Patch</b> - <span class=bsmall>posted by  <a class='nNewsMailLink' href='mailto:deathwatch@barrysworld.com'>Deathwatch</a> on Sat 14 July 2001 13:06:53 | <a href="comments.php?section=1&index=275">Comments (0)</a></span></td>
<td bgcolor="#CECECE" width=17><img src="images/item_icon.gif" width="17" height="17" alt="" border="0"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td bgcolor="#EEEEEE" colspan=2 class=news>
<table><tr><td valign=top><img src='images/icon_general.gif' alt='General News' border=0></td><td width="100%" valign=top>A new patch has been released for the <a href="http://opera.redeemsoft.com" class=colourise>Opera</a> mod for Half-Life and can be downloaded <a href="http://opera.redeemedsoft.com/_dl.htm?File=patches/Opera_Patch1b.zip" class=colourise>here</a>. (590kb)<br><br>This patch addresses serveral issues:<br><span class=quote><li> Believed to have fixed talking between living, dead and spectators.<br><li> Fixed mookmatch "bleeding crash" bug, where bleeding to death from a mook that has disappeared causes a crash.<br><li> Apparently, once again, believed to have fixed infinite round/match bugs. Believed to occur once "timelimit" or "fraglimit" is reached.<br><li> Meele attacks in "Dueling Beretta" do 35% normal damage.<br><li> "Suspect" players now do reduced damage with knives as well.<br><li> Added client-side "suspect" command that will give you a general idea of why you're a suspect.<br><li> [ESC] key gets you out of game menus spawned explicitly by the player.<br><li> Dedicated server can now see chat that's going on.<br><li> You can no longer choose the Tomcats with the "weapon_tomcat" command.<br><li> Forced penalties if you "team kill" for 1 second; any bonuses received within 1 second after you kill a team mate in MookMatch will be automatically deducted. Should deter this sort of activity real quick.</span><br><br>To help people out with crashes of the mod, they have posted a few hints as well to help solve these problems:<br><span class=quote>1) For the most part, this is a SERVER CRASH FIX. There are known issues with the client crashing, but those will be resolved once we can steadily reproduce them.<br><br>For the client crashes, there are some things you can do to help us solve the problem:<br><br>- Set "op_hud 0" in your CONFIG FILE, and see if it crashes then.<br>- Run in SOFTWARE MODE if you can to see if that crashes. I know it's a sacrifice, but it's the price you pay to have us try to help you.<br>   - Be as descriptive as you possibly can. Only saying "Half-Life crashed" doesn't help us; we need to know why, where, when.<br><br>2) Thie is BOTH a client DLL and a server DLL. By the client DLL changing, you will be UNABLE TO CONNECT TO NON-PATCHED SERVERS.</span><br><br>For those people who are being detected by Opera as <i>suspects</i> (the mod checks for known cheats, if found you will be tagged as suspect in the game and can't do any damage) and have no idea why, they have provided some help:<br><br><span class=quote>"In this patch, use the "suspect" command to determine where the files are being detected. If the detection occurs in "OPENGL32.DLL" and you are sure you aren't cheating, send me the DLL and I'll scan it myself. I've gotten reports of me detecting Asus drivers incorrectly, so I'm going out on a limb here and providing this service."</span><br><br>And a final notice from them:<br><span class=quote>"It's not a flawless patch, once again, but it's the best that we can make it."</span></td></tr></table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
