<td bgcolor="#CECECE" class="btext" width="100%"><b>Red Winter Review</b> - <span class=bsmall>posted by  <a class='nNewsMailLink' href='mailto:ice.m@btinternet.com'>ICE.M</a> on Wed 11 July 2001 14:01:45 | <a href="comments.php?section=1&index=254">Comments (0)</a></span></td>
<td bgcolor="#CECECE" width=17><img src="images/item_icon.gif" width="17" height="17" alt="" border="0"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td bgcolor="#EEEEEE" colspan=2 class=news>
<table><tr><td valign=top><img src='images/icon_general.gif' alt='General News' border=0></td><td width="100%" valign=top><a href="http://www.planethalflife.com" class=colourise target=_blank>Planet Half-Life</a> report that <a href="http://www.shockrealm.com/silentgames/" class=colourise target=_blank>Silent Games</a> has posted a <a href="http://www.shockrealm.com/silentgames/Previews/redwinter/redwinterpreview.html" class=colourise target=_blank>preview</a> of <a href="http://redwintermod.net/" class=colourise target=_blank>Red Winter</a>, which is an up-and-coming Half-Life mod. The preview has a number of screenshots from the game and talks in depth about all aspects of the game from the quality of maps to Addict ability. He concludes with the following paragraph:<br><br><span class=quote>Red Winter is gonna be a kick ass mod, right now its a blast to play and I can't wait to see what it's like with larger teams. The weapons are well done, although I would like to see more in the pistol department, sounds are great and always doesn't hurt to add more to satisfied my needs. Maps are great, models kick ass. I can't wait, oh wait I've already got the mod.</span><br><br>The <a href="http://redwintermod.net/" class=colourise target=_blank>Red Winter site</a> has also been updated with some <http://www.acid-drop.com/rw/Test2Screens1.shtml>screenshots</a> from a testing session that took place a couple of days ago. [I'm not sure about that URL, it could be to an old testing session but check it out anyway.</td></tr></table>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
</tr>
